OL,3,CPensioner died after being blown over
OL,4,Cby landing helicopter, jury told
OL,6,FIn a statement from her family, they
OL,7,Fdescribed how both Mrs Langan and her
OL,8,Fniece Gael were "blown over by
OL,9,Fdownwash from a helicopter".
OL,11,FThe statement, read to Exeter
OL,12,FCoroner's Court by retired senior
OL,13,Fcoroner Ian Arrow, said grandmother-of-
OL,14,Fthree Mrs Langan suffered fatal head
OL,15,Finjuries and died a short time later.
OL,17,FMr Arrow told the inquest jury that
OL,18,FMrs Langan, who was born in Liverpool,
OL,19,Fwas a retired civil servant who lived
OL,20,Fin Plymouth.
